Biography

As a freshman (2023):

Competed in 73 sets across 24 matches during her first collegiate season, earning two starts

Tallied 71 digs, 16 assists and three service aces in her debut season for the Terps

Made first collegiate action against Lamar (8/26), notching four digs

Dished out first career assist against Howard (9/10)

Recorded career-high three service aces against Le Moyne (9/15)

Made first collegiate starting lineup in Big Ten opener against No. 19 Purdue (9/22)

Picked up seven digs against Michigan (9/24)

Notched first-ever double-digit dig outing, tallying 13 against Northwestern (10/13)

Career-high three assists against Illinois (10/20)

Before Maryland:

2019, 2022, 2023 Redondo Power Classic All-Tournament Team and MVP

2021 First Place California Challenge

2021 Fifth Place CIF Open Division

2022 Second Place California Challenge

2022 Ranked Third in Southern CA, Ranked Fifth in CA

2022 Fist Place Atlanta Big South Qualifier (USA)

2021 First Place Las Vegas Red Rock Rave Qualifier Open

2021 First Place Premier Volleyball League

2019-2021 Volleyball Scholar Athlete Award

Personal:

Daughter of Lillian and Glen McGillivray

Dad played college hockey in Edmonton, Alberta Canada

Volunteers for soup kitchens, food banks, care package creation for veterans

Also played varsity beach volleyball at Torrey Pines High School

Plans to major in business

Updated November 27, 2023
